By Kingsley Chukwuka
Plateau only female Senator (APC Plateau South), Prof. Nora Dadu’ut, has again empowered the people of Plateau South Senatorial District with agricultural farm implements and Sustainable Development Goal (SDG), items with a total of 509 work tools aimed at adding colour to their lives.
Dadu’ut said the effort is in line with the fulfilment of her campaign promises which is focused on Agriculture, Education, Women/Youths Empowerment and Health/Human Capital Development.
The Senator was speaking on Saturday in Shendam Local Government Council of the State during the Distribution of the items.
“I am quite happy to be here today to distribute these items to the various beneficiaries and I strongly advise all the beneficiaries to put these items to proper use in order to better their lives”, she said.
Dadu’ut laud President Muhammadu Buhari for the economic policy of his administration and for his intervention in several ways to alleviate the concerns of the Nigerian populace.
“It is indeed through these interventions that I have attracted some of these benefits to my constituency.







